lsof -> list the open files and the processes that are using them, allowing you to identify which files are currently being accessed by which processes on the system.
lsof -i :80 -> lsof command with the -i option for list the open files that are associated with network connections on port 80, allowing you to identify which processes are using

netstat -> netstat command for display network connections, routing tables, and interface statistics, allowing you to monitor and troubleshoot network activity on your system.


nslookup -> nslookup command for query the Domain Name System (DNS) to obtain information about domain names, IP addresses, and other DNS records, allowing you to troubleshoot DNS-related issues and gather information about network resources.
